I made this recipe with pluots (cross between a plum and apricot - new fruit I had never had before!) for a New Year's Day brunch. It was super simple and looked elegant with a dusting of confectionery sugar. Fit in perfectly with savory dishes because it is not too sweet. Even my nine year old niece gobbled it up. Only change I would make next time is to combine turbinado sugar with the cinnamon to give it a little crunch.

