Rating: 3
I've made this quite a few times with several types of fruit. As it has evolved for me, I've taken to topping the cake with the sliced plums, dispensing with the cinnamon-sugar and adding 1 or 2 chopped plums to the batter. The plums on top almost have a jam-like consistency and it looks almost pretty enough to display permanently, if, of course I could stop eating it. This variation came out of buying some very ripe Satsuma plums that were very terribly difficult to pit, so in case anyone runs into that issue this small variant may be worth a go.

Rating: 3
A great recipe--made it using pears I picked from my front yard. (If you use pears in this recipe, just made sure you use a firm type so they don't turn to mush in the oven.) A delicious dessert, and it would make a great breakfast cake because it's not too sweet.

